==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: echoic
<hw>echoic</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(linguistics)</fld>
<def>Formed in imitation of a natural sound; -- of words. Contrasted to
<ant>nonechoic</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> imitative, onomatopoeic, onomatopoeical,
onomatopoetic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like or characteristic of an echo.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> echolike.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>echoing</ent>⟦br⟧
